[metadata]
title: I Tested the Luna Ultra for 60 Days!
channel: @octopusinc_
source: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=agU64B9cblc
upload_date: 20260611
transcript_source: captions
route: text

---

[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is the new Insta 360 Luna Ultra. And while it might look like another pocket camera, this thing packs some seriously impressive features. We\'re talking 8K video, 10bit eyelog recording, a dedicated telephoto lens for zooming in and out, and maybe my'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'favorite feature, a touch screen that actually detaches from the camera and becomes a wireless remote monitor and even a microphone. So, in this video, I\'m going to show you everything you need to know about the new Luna Ultra. A'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'big thanks to Insta3 for partnering with us on this video and sending out the Luna Ultra for review and testing. Now, let\'s just dive straight into looking at some of the footage that you can shoot with this camera. So, this footage is'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'probably my favorite footage I\'ve seen out of an Insta 360 product so far. I have several of their cameras. All of them I enjoy using, but the Luna Ultra just feels a little bit more cinematic when you look at its image. The larger 1'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in sensor that\'s inside of the Luna Ultra is really going to help with some of that background subject separation and background blur that you get with a larger sensor. And you pair that with the focal lengths that have been'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'co-engineered with Leica, which we\'ll talk about just a little bit later. But this image quality is looking fantastic. You get 14 stops of dynamic range if you shoot in the EyLog color profile. or you can just shoot with the standard picture'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'profile that looks great straight out of camera if you\'re not somebody who wants to tweak with all of your colors and color grade. So, I know for a lot of beginners, you would just choose the standard profile and it looks really good. Now, for resolutions, you can record in up to 8K at 30 frames per'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'second with this camera. So, I mean, it\'s an insane amount of resolution and detail you can get out of the Luna Ultra. And you can also record in a Dolby Vision color mode, which just preserves a ton of highlight and shadow'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'detail. It gives the footage a more premium HDR look on different supported displays if you want to shoot in Dolby Vision. And then 8K, of course, is going to give you a ton of flexibility for cropping and refframing in'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'post-production. I think most people will be fine with the 4K format. In 4K, you can record up to 120 frames per second to get some ultra slow motion shooting. And then if you bump down to 1080p, you can bump that up to 240'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'frames per second. Now, this is actually the first Insta 360 camera that\'s able to shoot in 10bit color. So, that just is going to preserve a lot of color information for color grading your footage in post-production. Especially'

[02:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'when you shoot in the log color profile, you get a ton of dynamic range and color information to work with out of this 10 bit sensor. We did some beta testing early on with this camera in the EyeLog profile and the colors definitely leaned'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a little bit towards like the yellowy green side, but since then there\'s been a couple of firmware updates for this camera and the color looks a lot better straight out of a camera in the log profile. But again, still you have to color grade this footage. That\'s the'

[02:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'whole point of iLog is to give you a really flat image to work with so that colorists can grade this in post-production. So you kind of have to know what you\'re doing to work with log footage already. But there\'s even some conversion ls that Insta3 provides for you if you want to convert your footage'

[02:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pretty quickly. And overall, the Luna Ultra to me just feels like Insta 360\'s most serious camera so far in terms of image quality and performance with that 10- bit sensor. Now, let\'s zoom in a little bit on the design of the Luna'

[03:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Ultra. As soon as you get this thing in the hand, you\'ll realize right away, even like with the case on it, as you open the case up, everything just feels more professional and rugged compared to some other pocket style cameras that I\'ve used in the past. A lot of times'

[03:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'these tiny gimbal cameras feel a little bit lightweight, like they\'re going to break pretty easily. But to me, this has a more premium, professional feel straight out of the box. When we first featured the Luna Ultra on the channel, a lot of people pointed out that the'

[03:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lens element looks a lot like Wall-E. And once you see it, like honestly, you can\'t unsee it. So, it kind of has Wall-E vibes from the Disney movie. And honestly, I don\'t hate it. I like Wall-E. Wall-ally is a cool guy. It also comes with this nice hard shell carrying'

[03:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'case. If you don\'t want to bring the entire padded case that comes in the combo kit, you can just carry it around this little hard shell carrying case. And there\'s even spots where you could mount like the Insta 360 mic pro on top. And then inside of the case, there\'s a'

[03:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'spot for the black mist filter and a wide angle lens filter that you\'re able to pair with the Luna Ultra as well. Also, if you get this kit, you get an extended battery grip, which is great to extend the battery life of the Luna'

[04:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Ultra, or you could use the smaller just base adapter. But what\'s cool about both of these options are they have a little builtin mini tripod to them. And it\'s kind of weird, honestly. It\'s like they kind of feel like a paper clip. They\'re'

[04:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'not the most robust thing I\'ve ever seen, but it\'s nice that you have just a built-in tripod to either one of those. And then there\'s quarter 20 threads on the base of these as well. If you wanted to mount them to tripods or screw in a more robust mini tripod to the bottom of'

[04:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'these, you could do that. And it also comes with one Insta3 mic pro, which is their latest wireless microphone that\'s very professional. 32-bit float and uses e- in display to customize the look and feel of your microphone externally,'

[04:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which is really cool. We have a full video I\'ll link in the description of this video about the mic pro. Fantastic microphone, and I\'m actually using it right now inside of this little wireless mic handle for this video. There\'s also 47 GB of internal storage with the Luna'

[05:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Ultra. So, this is fantastic. if you forget your micro SD card or that fills up for whatever reason, you actually have 47 gigs that you can use as internal storage for a backup. And'

[05:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually, my first couple days of shooting with this camera, I had no SD card inside of it, and I just relied on the internal storage, and I got well over an hour of 4K footage recorded on that 47 GB. Some people, of course, will'

[05:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'wish it was like over a 100 gigs of internal storage, but I\'m just glad they gave us anything. 47 gigs is way better than having no internal storage at all. Okay, let\'s talk about the fact how there are two lenses on the Luna Ultra. Most mini gimbal style cameras like this'

[05:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'essentially have one focal length and a lot of times they use digital zoom if you want to crop into your image at all and get a tighter shot. But the Luna Ultra actually gives you a dedicated telephoto camera. This is incredible.'

[05:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, as soon as you bump in to 3x zoom, it switches over to the telephoto lens to get you better image quality. So, you\'re not just relying fully on digital zoom. In all of my testing, I actually'

[06:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really enjoyed the image quality of the 3x lens. It just provides a different kind of focal length that I\'m not really used to seeing on pocket style cameras. A lot of times it\'s just that ultra wide sort of view that you have for vlogging.'

[06:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'But adding this 3x telephoto lens just gives you way more depth of field and background separation for isolating subjects when you\'re recording videos. And you can also digitally zoom even further up to six times for lossless zoom. So really the quality isn\'t really'

[06:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'going to degrade at all, even up to six times. And then if you want to really push it, you can go up to 12 times zoom. And I did some testing with this at an airport where I was like tracking airport employees when I was traveling. And dude, this thing at 12x is'

[06:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'incredible. It actually tracks really well still. All of the software works really well and the image quality is actually passable at 12x zoom. And then when you zoom back out to like 1x, it\'s actually crazy how far a 12x zoom is on'

[06:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a pocket style camera. I think a lot of people are going to have fun using these variety of focal lengths. And also, the stabilization actually worked really well even when you\'re zoomed in. So, if you\'re somebody who wants tighter shots, but you\'re going to still be walking and'

[07:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'moving around, the stabilization still works great. Now, I do want to talk about some low light performance because in my testing, the low light capabilities of the Luna Ultra are actually pretty solid. So, there\'s a specific mode to that this camera is'

[07:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'able to shoot in called pure video mode. It\'s specifically built for low light shooting. So, I\'d encourage you if you\'re going to use this camera or other Insta 360 products, put the camera in pure video mode to get the best results.'

[07:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This leverages AI processing and noise reduction to give you the cleanest video file, but also increases your detail retention so that you\'re not getting like a super cakey smooth image in lower light situations. And in this mode,'

[07:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you\'re able to film in 4K up to 60 frames per second for even some slow motion lower light shooting. Now, image results for low light were probably what I would expect. It is a smaller sensor compared to something like my Sony FX3, which is a full-frame 12 megapixel'

[07:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lowlight monster. So, yeah, you\'re not going to get like full-frame mirrorless camera level of low light performance, but it\'s still going to be passable for most situations. If you\'re just vlogging in a restaurant at a lower light condition, it\'s going to still look'

[08:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pretty good. Okay, let\'s talk about maybe my favorite feature of the Luna Ultra, which is its detachable screen. This is like to me the most innovative feature of the Luna Ultra. So, it\'s a removable touchcreen that allows you to monitor your video signal for wireless'

[08:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'monitoring. So, if you want to walk away from your camera, and I\'ve done this in like multiple different environments. I\'ve been like 30, 40, 50 plus feet away from my camera and I can still see a clean feed of my video signal. Totally'

[08:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'fine. But beyond that, it\'s also a wireless camera control. So, I can still zoom in, start and stop recording, access the menus, and change different settings all remotely and not having to be tied down to where my camera is. And'

[08:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a bonus feature that\'s really cool is there\'s actually a built-in microphone at the top of the monitor that you can use to record audio if you\'re further away from your camera. And I\'ll show you some audio tests with that in just a minute. I find myself using this'

[09:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'detachable feature a ton when I\'m trying to get creative angles of myself. It\'s great for solo creators who want to add more creative angles to their productions and vlogs and videos while still making sure their framing is correct. And this might be the feature'

[09:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that most people maybe kind of underrate. And yeah, it\'s like maybe kind of cool, but once you actually practically get this in the hand and start using it, it\'s super fun to use. Now, let\'s talk about stabilization and tracking with the Luna Ultra. Of course,'

[09:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this camera is actually on a gimbal as well, which is a physical gimbal. So, it uses hardware to stabilize your image versus other cameras. And maybe you\'ve used like GoPro style action cameras in the past that maybe use digital'

[09:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stabilization or even your smartphone uses digital stabilization that uses software to stabilize your image. This is an actual piece of hardware that is stabilizing your shot to make it look ultra smooth. In all of my stabilization'

[09:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'testing with the Luna Ultra, results are super smooth. And there\'s actually some different modes you can put the camera into to lock off different axises. Like you could lock off the pan axis if you wanted to or the tilt axis. You can'

[10:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'control all of those things with the Luna Ultra. I\'ll show you a few quick control tests so you can see what this looks like in different situations. First is just walking straight forward with the camera to test its stabilization in a pretty normal pace.'

[10:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The next test is me actually running pretty fast with the Luna Ultra just to see if the stabilization can keep up or if as I move up and down if it gets kind of warpy or anything, and I\'m not actually seeing that with the Luna'

[10:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Ultra. So, that\'s a big win for people who are doing action style sports or other things that require faster motion. And here are a few tests of me tracking with the camera. And you can see that the tracking feature works really well for a variety of situations. I did this'

[10:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'at the airport. I also did a test at this like farm fair that my family went to where these dogs were like hurting sheep and it was like tracking this fast dog that was hurting sheep all around which was super hilarious and weird.'

[10:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Something I did see in my testing if you walk directly behind an object and your face is obstructed between the view of you and the Luna Ultra. It can lock off for you for a second and try to figure out where you went. But once you pop'

[11:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'back out and get eyesight with the camera, it can usually lock back on you and continue tracking. So now I want to do a series of audio tests. Testing first the internal microphone on the Luna Ultra. So I am just speaking'

[11:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'directly into the camera right now and there\'s no external microphones attached. This is just what the built-in audio sounds like with the Luna Ultra and honestly it sounds really solid. Now for this next test, we\'re doing something a little bit different. I\'ve'

[11:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually detached the wireless monitoring remote. But what\'s interesting about this remote is there\'s actually a microphone on the top of it. So, right now, the audio that you\'re hearing is actually from the monitoring remote itself with the built-in'

[11:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'microphone, and this is what it sounds like. And in all of my testing initially that I\'ve done, the audio actually sounds really solid. Like, this is for sure a usable source of audio. So, if you need to be further away from your camera, but you don\'t have an external'

[11:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'microphone, you can still get some quality audio with this built-in mic on the monitor. And if you really want to step up your audio, the Luna Ultra pairs natively with their Mic Pro that newly was released. This microphone even has a'

[12:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cool e- in display, so you can change the logo on the microphone to whatever logo you want it to be, or you could just keep it like black or white if you wanted to have it a solid color as well. And if you\'re really on a budget, you'

[12:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'could also pair this with the Insta3 mic air. So that\'s even a more affordable microphone that still sounds really good. So multiple mic options that just pair natively with the Luna Ultra and you don\'t need a wireless receiver. So, if I had any suggestions or feedback'

[12:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that I\'d give Insta 360 for improvements with the Luna Ultra, I would say first and foremost, as I shoot in the EyLog color profile, sometimes I still feel like the skin tones are a little bit off depending on my shooting environment,'

[12:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'especially if there\'s a lot of like greens and yellows in the scene, a lot of natural trees and colors like that, it can kind of bleed into the image and make my skin tones feel a little bit yellow or green. And in our beta'

[12:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'testing, this was super prevalent. But since then, they\'ve actually made several adjustments to the color for their conversion LUTs and even the internal way that the camera processes log footage. So, I think it actually looks way better. And again, I\'ve showed'

[13:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you a lot of EyLog footage in this review that actually looks great straight out of the camera with a simple color correction L. But just something I wanted to note here. And the second thing is just I want to make sure that the software and the app experience is dialed in before this gets in the hands'

[13:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of consumers because my review unit I had several issues pairing it with the app or getting it updated to the latest firmware and sometimes I would like turn on the camera and try to hit record and I get like a weird glitch. And all of'

[13:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this is stuff that can be improved with firmware updates prior to launch. I get that this is a brand new product from them and they\'re going to work out all of those kinks before launch, but I just want to be transparent about what my experience has been and overall it\'s'

[13:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'been very positive. Just a couple few quirks here and there. So, who should purchase the Luna Ultra? Well, if you\'re a travel creator, a vlog creator, or you just want to film yourself with a more prolevel feel than maybe other pocket cameras have been in the past, this is a'

[13:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'great option. Also, if you live in the United States, you currently are able to purchase this camera versus other companies like DJI right now. You\'re not able Like I literally could not go out and buy the DJI Pocket 4 right now, even'

[14:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'if I wanted to because of where I live. But the Luna Ultra will be available in the United States, which is a huge plus for us living in the USA. Also, if you want multiple focal lengths and don\'t want your pocket camera just to have'

[14:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that wide-angle look, if you want that tighter look and feel out of your compositions, this is a great choice. And of course, if you already have some other Insta3 products, like some of their other cameras and you\'re used to those, or you have one of their'

[14:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'microphones like the mic air or the mic pro, this would be a great addition to your creator kit. If you want to check out the Insta3 Luna Ultra, you can click the link down in the description below to check it out. And if you want to see our full review on the microphone that'

[14:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pairs great with this camera, the Insta3 Mic Pro. I will link that right here on screen so you can check out that review. and I\'ll see you in the next'
